<< Git Pull and Push Branches >>

< Main Branch Preparation >
- The team leader should create a new GitHub repo.
- Each member of the team should clone this repo to their local computer. ğŸš¨git clone <HTTPS link>

- The team leader creates a file on main branch (local computer) add commit a file called "data_exploration.py" 
  and then push their changes to GitHub. ğŸš¨git add . â¡ï¸ git commit -m '<description of the commit>' â¡ï¸ git push
- Team members should then pull these changes to their local machines. ğŸš¨ git pull

< Each member Sub Branch Preparation >
- each team member should create a new sub branch "<name>/branching_exercise" ğŸš¨ git checkout -b <name>/branching_exercise 
  checkout : move to another branch or move to previous commit
  checkout -b : while creating a branch moving to the branch at the sametime
- each team member should add and commit a file "<name>.txt" on each sub branch and commit ğŸš¨git add . â¡ï¸ git commit -m '<description of the commit>'
- each team member should push their respective branches to GitHub. ğŸš¨git push origin <name>/branching_exercise

< Each member wants to modify other team member's file >
- each team member should checkout the main branch. ğŸš¨ git checkout main  : Move to main brtanch
- Make sure branch list on local computer and remote repository ğŸš¨ git branch -a
- Maks sure current located branch name ğŸš¨ git status
- While on main, everyone should create a new branch with the name of the branch you want to check on local computer ğŸš¨ git checkout -b <name of your colleague>/branching_exercise
- At the moment, this branch is empty, so you need to pull the branch of your colleague into your computer. ğŸš¨ git pull origin <name of your colleague>/branching_exercise


<< Merging Into main locally >>
- each team member should checkout main. ğŸš¨git checkout main
- Maks sure current located branch name ğŸš¨ git status ===> SHOULD BE "MAIN"
- merge the branch that theyâ€™ve created and named into main. ğŸš¨ git merge <name>/branching_exercise
- each team member should push their changes to GitHub.ğŸš¨git push origin. Try to go one by one.
  ğŸ”‘ If Git refuses to push, run git pull, and try again
- Once everyone has pushed their changes to GitHub, each team member should pull the repository. ğŸš¨git pull
- delete the branch that you were working on. ğŸš¨git branch -d <name>/branching_exercise


<< Merging Into main remote github >>
- After pulling the updated main branch, each team member should create a new branch on local computerğŸš¨ git checkout -b <name>/<name of feature>
- Add or change anything you'd like on this branch. ğŸš¨git add . â¡ï¸ git commit -m '<description of the commit>'
